<div class="callout">
  <div class="callout-title">Anchor question</div>
  How do scientists know what they know — and how should we know what we know?
</div>

<div class="prose">
  <p>The anchor skill for the whole year is <strong>OPVL</strong> — Origin / Purpose / Value / Limitations. We learn it here, in low stakes, on contested topics you already have opinions about. We come back to it in every subsequent unit at increasing difficulty.</p>
  <p>The other big move is the <strong>AI Documentation Protocol</strong> — AI is treated as a source, OPVL'd like any other, and documented in a structured template that goes with every deliverable. The aim is not to police AI use but to build the metacognitive habit that makes AI use valuable instead of dangerous.</p>
</div>

